<item>
            <title>[DATACMNS-117] Add HandlerMethodArgumentResolver alternative to the PageableArgumentResolver</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATACMNS-117</link>
                <project id="10510" key="DATACMNS">Spring Data Commons</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It is recommended to re-implement &lt;tt&gt;WebArgumentResolver&lt;/tt&gt; types as &lt;tt&gt;HandlerMethodArgumentResolver&lt;/tt&gt; in Spring 3.1. Although a &lt;tt&gt;WebArgumentResolver&lt;/tt&gt; is adapted transparently to the new contract, as the javadoc for &lt;tt&gt;AbstractWebArgumentResolverAdapter&lt;/tt&gt; indicates, a &lt;tt&gt;HandlerMethodArgumentResolver.supportsParameter(MethodParameter)&lt;/tt&gt; method can only be implemented by actually calling &lt;tt&gt;WebArgumentResolver.resolve()&lt;/tt&gt; and checking if the return value is &lt;tt&gt;UNRESOLVED&lt;/tt&gt;. If an exception occurs during that check, it isn&apos;t clear if the failure is because the parameter can not be supported or whether there was some other real failure. As a result the exception has to be absorbed and other resolvers given a chance instead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
